<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12925] AssertionError executing authz stmt on UDF without keyspace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12925</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Performing a &lt;tt&gt;GRANT&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;REVOKE&lt;/tt&gt; on a user defined function requires the function name to be qualified by its keyspace. Unlike &lt;tt&gt;GRANT/REVOKE&lt;/tt&gt; on a table, the keyspace cannot be inferred from the &lt;tt&gt;ClientState&lt;/tt&gt; as it&apos;s needed by the parser to either lookup the function (in 2.2), or convert the function arguments from CQL types to their corresponding &lt;tt&gt;AbstractType&lt;/tt&gt; (in 3.0+).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, performing such a statement results in an unhandled assert error and a &lt;tt&gt;ServerError&lt;/tt&gt; response to the client.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
